OL,3,CSats 'devastating' for Send pupils,
OL,4,CMotherland star and parent campaigners
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FShe called for a more inclusive
OL,8,Fapproach that recognised children's
OL,9,Fmental health and individual needs.
OL,11,F"This is a systemic failing within our
OL,12,Fassessment system, not the fault of
OL,13,Fany individual teacher or
OL,14,Fheadteacher," she said.
OL,16,FIn 2025, some 24% of children with
OL,17,FSend passed their Sats by meeting the
OL,18,Fexpected standards in reading, writing
OL,19,Fand maths.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@MO]
