OL,4,CMotherland star and parent campaigners
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FPolling of 520 Send parents whose
OL,8,Fchildren did not reach the expected
OL,9,Fstandard in Sats by Omnisis for
OL,10,Fcampaign group More Than A Score found
OL,11,Ftwo-thirds (67%) said Sats results
OL,12,Fnegatively impacted their child
OL,13,Fwanting to go to school.
OL,15,FHalf also said their child's self-
OL,16,Festeem was damaged, and that they
OL,17,Fbelieved Sats would have a lasting
OL,18,Fnegative impact.
